{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4e5e8a2-c4ed-4943-8226-e9d7631c166e","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pins the exception to the exact call\n- You can inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2bd8f3b4-c5c6-4e01-a67f-e9c24d15ba3e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a straightforward knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":232,"requestId":"0828:1E7A6A:849B1E8:9301C3A:69EAC61A"},"id":"bcf9c686-61bb-4a16-957a-f04f62528bb4","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:23:43.620Z","parentId":"ce9e762d-23bc-4725-9a68-8f57e53d9357"}
